Place the peas, onion, garlic and mint leaves into a food processor and blend to a thick pur√©e.Add the yoghurt and blend again, leaving the mixture slightly lumpy.Transfer the mixture to a bowl and stir in the chilli, cumin, coriander and lime juice and season, to taste, with salt and freshly ground black pepper.Spoon into a serving bowl and drizzle with the olive oil. Serve with a bowl of nachos alongside for dipping.